---
/**
 * CTXone Early Access Program (EAP) landing page.
 *
 * Target audience: organizations in compliance-forward industries
 * (healthcare, financial services, regulated public sector, large
 * SaaS) deploying AI agents internally at scale. The page pitches
 * anchor-partner terms — 3yr commitment, locked early rate, direct
 * founder access, roadmap influence — without publishing pricing
 * (pricing is private, shared in the qualification call).
 *
 * The "Apply" form is wired as a client-side mailto: composer — no
 * backend. Submits open the user's mail client addressed to
 * hello@agentstatelabs.com with the form fields pre-filled as the
 * body. Good enough for v1; easy to swap for a real form backend
 * once there's volume.
 */
import LandingLayout from '../layouts/LandingLayout.astro';
---

<LandingLayout
	title="CTXone Early Access Program — Enterprise anchor partners"
	description="For organizations deploying AI agents internally at scale, today. Direct founder access, roadmap influence, locked early pricing for 3 years."
>
	<section class="section">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<div class="eyebrow">Early Access Program</div>
			<h1>Early Access Program</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				For organizations deploying AI agents internally at
				scale — today, not in 12 months.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<h2>What it is</h2>
			<p>
				CTXone's open tier is shipping and ready to install
				today. CTXone Enterprise — multi-tenant, SSO, audit
				bundles, compliance features — is on a compressed
				roadmap. The Early Access Program is how we work with
				a small number of anchor partners to ship Enterprise
				features that actually solve their problems, rather
				than what we guess.
			</p>
			<p>
				EAP partners run on CTXone today, shape what ships
				next, and lock their rate for 3 years. We pick up the
				phone when they call. That's the whole program.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<h2>What partners get</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Immediate access to the CTXone open tier</strong>
					— install it, evaluate it, run it against your real
					workflows starting today.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Early access to Enterprise features as they ship</strong>
					— SSO, RBAC, audit bundles, multi-tenant, policy
					governance, fleet view — at no additional cost
					during the EAP period.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Direct founder access</strong> — email,
					shared Slack, whatever works for you. Feedback,
					support, and bug triage go straight to the people
					building the product.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Quarterly product review calls</strong> —
					30-60 minutes every quarter. Your input shapes the
					Enterprise roadmap.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Locked early pricing, guaranteed for 3 years</strong>
					— the rate you commit at holds regardless of
					future GA pricing changes.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Co-authored case study (opt-in only)</strong>
					— marketing visibility when you're ready, never
					before.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<h2>Who it's for</h2>
			<p>
				Organizations in compliance-forward industries —
				healthcare, financial services, regulated public
				sector, large SaaS — that are actively building
				internal agent workflows and need Enterprise features
				in the short-to-medium term. Partners who want to
				help shape the product, not just consume a finished
				SaaS offering.
			</p>
			<p>
				If you're a solo dev or hobbyist, the
				<a href="/getting-started/quickstart/">open tier</a>
				is what you want — it's the same product, minus the
				Enterprise bolt-ons. EAP is for teams with commercial
				intent and a real deployment.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<h2>What partners commit to</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>3-year minimum term</strong> at the locked
					rate.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>One 30-60 minute feedback call per quarter</strong>
					— so we can tell whether we're building the right
					thing.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Willingness to be a reference</strong> —
					verbal or written, if the fit is right. No
					unilateral marketing use of your name.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Actual usage</strong> — you use CTXone as
					part of your real workflow. The program isn't
					set up to reserve a future rate on code you don't
					intend to run.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<h2>Apply</h2>
			<p class="form-lede">
				Fill out the form below. We'll reply within two
				business days to schedule a qualification call.
			</p>

			<form id="eap-form" class="eap-form" novalidate>
				<div class="field">
					<label for="company">Company name</label>
					<input
						type="text"
						id="company"
						name="company"
						autocomplete="organization"
						required
					/>
				</div>

				<div class="field-row">
					<div class="field">
						<label for="name">Your name</label>
						<input
							type="text"
							id="name"
							name="name"
							autocomplete="name"
							required
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="field">
						<label for="role">Your role</label>
						<input
							type="text"
							id="role"
							name="role"
							autocomplete="organization-title"
							placeholder="e.g. VP Engineering"
							required
						/>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="field">
					<label for="email">Email</label>
					<input
						type="email"
						id="email"
						name="email"
						autocomplete="email"
						required
					/>
				</div>

				<div class="field">
					<label for="use-case">
						Primary use case <span class="hint">(~200 chars)</span>
					</label>
					<textarea
						id="use-case"
						name="use-case"
						rows="3"
						maxlength="220"
						placeholder="What internal agent workflow are you building?"
						required></textarea>
				</div>

				<div class="field">
					<label for="team-size">Team size</label>
					<select id="team-size" name="team-size" required>
						<option value="">Select a range…</option>
						<option value="1-10">1-10 engineers</option>
						<option value="10-50">10-50 engineers</option>
						<option value="50+">50+ engineers</option>
					</select>
				</div>

				<fieldset class="field field-checks">
					<legend>Compliance requirements</legend>
					<label class="check">
						<input type="checkbox" name="compliance" value="HIPAA" />
						<span>HIPAA</span>
					</label>
					<label class="check">
						<input type="checkbox" name="compliance" value="SOC 2" />
						<span>SOC 2</span>
					</label>
					<label class="check">
						<input type="checkbox" name="compliance" value="GDPR" />
						<span>GDPR</span>
					</label>
					<label class="check">
						<input
							type="checkbox"
							name="compliance"
							value="SOX / FINRA"
						/>
						<span>SOX / FINRA</span>
					</label>
					<label class="check">
						<input
							type="checkbox"
							name="compliance"
							value="Data residency"
						/>
						<span>Data residency</span>
					</label>
					<label class="check">
						<input type="checkbox" name="compliance" value="Other" />
						<span>None / other</span>
					</label>
				</fieldset>

				<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Apply</button>
				<p class="form-note">
					Submitting opens your mail client with a pre-filled
					message to
					<code>hello@agentstatelabs.com</code>.
				</p>
			</form>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<h2>FAQ</h2>

			<div class="faq">
				<h3>What if I'm not sure we qualify?</h3>
				<p>
					Fill out the form anyway — we triage, and if the
					fit isn't right we'll point you at the self-serve
					open tier. No one loses anything by asking.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq">
				<h3>How many partners are you taking?</h3>
				<p>
					A small number. Enough to get real signal, few
					enough that every partner gets founder-level
					attention. We'd rather have five committed
					partners than fifty disengaged ones.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq">
				<h3>Is pricing public?</h3>
				<p>
					No, because the right anchor is per-partner. We
					quote after understanding your use case, team
					size, and compliance needs on the qualification
					call.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq">
				<h3>When does Enterprise GA ship?</h3>
				<p>
					We don't commit externally to a date yet. EAP
					partners get features as they ship and transition
					on their locked rate when Enterprise reaches GA.
				</p>
			</div>

			<p class="more">
				Questions that aren't listed here? Email
				<a href="mailto:hello@agentstatelabs.com">
					hello@agentstatelabs.com
				</a>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</LandingLayout>

<script is:inline>
	// Client-side mailto composer. Collects the form fields, encodes
	// them into a mailto: URL addressed to hello@agentstatelabs.com,
	// and hands it to the browser to open in the user's mail client.
	// No backend, no third-party form service — deliberately minimal
	// for v1. Works even with JavaScript disabled as long as the user
	// actively submits (the form will just POST nowhere; we swap to a
	// mailto: target in that case via the `action` below).
	(function () {
		var form = document.getElementById('eap-form');
		if (!form) return;

		form.addEventListener('submit', function (event) {
			event.preventDefault();
			var data = new FormData(form);
			var compliance = data.getAll('compliance').join(', ') || 'None specified';

			var lines = [
				'Company: ' + (data.get('company') || ''),
				'Contact: ' + (data.get('name') || '') + ' (' + (data.get('role') || '') + ')',
				'Email: ' + (data.get('email') || ''),
				'Team size: ' + (data.get('team-size') || ''),
				'Compliance: ' + compliance,
				'',
				'Primary use case:',
				data.get('use-case') || '',
			];

			var subject = 'CTXone Early Access — ' + (data.get('company') || 'Inquiry');
			var body = lines.join('\n');
			var href =
				'mailto:hello@agentstatelabs.com' +
				'?subject=' + encodeURIComponent(subject) +
				'&body=' + encodeURIComponent(body);

			window.location.href = href;
		});
	})();
</script>

<style>
	.narrow {
		max-width: 44rem;
	}

	.eyebrow {
		color: var(--ctx-accent);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
		font-weight: 800;
		color: #ffffff;
		margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
		line-height: 1.15;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.3rem;
		color: #ffffff;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
	}

	h3 {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: #ffffff;
		margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;
	}

	p {
		color: var(--ctx-text);
		font-size: 1rem;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.lede {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		margin: 0;
	}

	ul {
		color: var(--ctx-text);
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	ul li {
		margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
	}

	strong {
		color: #ffffff;
	}

	code {
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-sm);
		font-size: 0.9em;
		color: var(--ctx-accent-text);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.form-lede {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.eap-form {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.25rem;
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
		padding: 1.75rem;
	}

	.field {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.4rem;
	}

	.field-row {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 560px) {
		.field-row {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	label,
	legend {
		color: #ffffff;
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
	}

	legend {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		padding: 0;
	}

	.hint {
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		font-weight: 400;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-sans);
		letter-spacing: 0;
	}

	input[type='text'],
	input[type='email'],
	textarea,
	select {
		background: var(--ctx-bg);
		color: var(--ctx-text);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border-hi);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-md);
		padding: 0.65rem 0.8rem;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-sans);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		width: 100%;
	}

	textarea {
		resize: vertical;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-sans);
	}

	input:focus,
	textarea:focus,
	select:focus {
		outline: none;
		border-color: var(--ctx-accent);
		box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);
	}

	.field-checks {
		border: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}

	.check {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-sans);
		font-weight: 400;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		letter-spacing: 0;
		cursor: pointer;
	}

	.check input[type='checkbox'] {
		width: auto;
		margin: 0;
		accent-color: var(--ctx-accent);
	}

	button[type='submit'] {
		align-self: flex-start;
		border: none;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-sans);
	}

	.form-note {
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.form-note code {
		font-size: 0.85em;
	}

	.faq {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.more {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
</style>
